frameDefinitions: A specified Designer or a Brand creates and distributes a Collection of related Products.
This frame contains nouns denoting Aggregates of Individuals.
The words in this frame describe entities that occur in some temporally-ordered sequence.
This frame contains LUs that express the Form which a piece of Artwork represents.
An Assailant physically attacks a Victim (which is usually but not always sentient), causing or intending to cause the Victim physical damage.
This frame has to do with nouns denoting types of entities.
frameExamples: The new Gucci <t>line</t> is due out in early Spring.
An <t><fex name='Agg'>army</fex></t> of postal workers descended on my office.
Describe in detail the <t>sequence</t> of steps taken during an emergency.
Her <t>style</t> of painting is an excellent blend of traditional and modern.
As soon as he stepped out of the bar he was <t>set</t> upon by four men in ski-masks.
I don't like this newfangled <t><fex name='Subtype'>kind</fex></t> of  fish.
listRoleDefinitions: The company that produces the <fen>Collection</fen> of <fen>Products</fen>.
The set of <fen>Products</fen> produced by the <fen>Brand</fen>.
The individual items produced by the <fen>Brand</fen>.
The person who designs the <fen>Collection</fen>.
This role identifies the people or things that form  the <fen>Aggregate</fen>.
This role identifies the collection of entities that are the <fen>Aggregate</fen>.
This entity occurs in some sequence with <fen>Entity_2</fen>.
This entity occurs in some sequence with respect to <fen>Entity_1</fen>.
<fen>Entities</fen> that occur in some temporal order.
A characterization of the sequence in which the entities occur.
A person who creates an <fen>Artwork</fen> with a particular recognizable <fen>Form</fen>.
A created artifact that is created by an <fen>Artist</fen> and has a unique <fen>Form</fen> as perceived by some judge.

The <fen>Form</fen> is a style that characterizes an <fen>Artwork</fen> (or an <fen>Artist</fen>, metonymically) and can be recognized by a judge. This role is usually incorporated into the target for nouns in this frame.
A description of when the <fen>Artwork</fen> was created.
This role is the being or entity that is injured by the <fen>Assailant</fen>'s attack.
The person (or other self-directed entity) that is attempting physical harm to the <fen>Victim</fen>.
This role identifies the time when the <fen>Assailant</fen> attacks the <fen>Victim</fen>.
This role identifies the place where the <fen>Assailant</fen> makes an assault on the <fen>Victim</fen>.
The entity which denotes a subtype of the more general <fen>Category</fen>.
The more general type that the target denotes a subtype of. This role is obligatory and should be labeled DNI when not present.
listRoleExamples: Did you see the new <fex>Kate Spade</fex> line?
They're so damn rich, they could buy this whole <fex><t>line</t></fex> without batting an eyelash.
Jaques just showed us his Fall line <fex>of cocktail dresses</fex>.
A crowd <fex>of hoodlums</fex> filled the plaza.
A <fex><t>crowd</t></fex> of hoodlums filled the plaza.
The study consisted of a <fex>chronologically varied</fex> SERIES of grotesque heads.
The mysterious fighter attacked <fex>the guardsmen</fex> with a sabre.
<fex>The mysterious fighter</fex> attacked the guardsmen with a sabre.
<fex>As soon as he stepped out of the bar</fex> he was set upon by four men in ski-masks.
Then Jon-O's forces ambushed them <fex>on the left flank</fex> from a line of low hills.
I don't like this <fex>kind</fex> of fish.
They created a new breed <fex>of dog</fex>.
